title: 'Cash at home' row: SC uploads video of burnt notes, HC CJ suggests deeper probe; Varma cries conspiracy
'Choksi in Belgium, India eyes extradition'

description: JAC demands freeze on LS seats based on 1971 census population by another 25 years
title: CMs rally against Centre's proposed population-based delimitation
Relief for farmers, exporters as govt scraps 20% export duty on onions
Sinister play of mind games, fabrication & isolation driving ‘digital arrest’ scams
Waris member held for 2023 thana attack

description: The CBI has closed the investigation into actor Sushant Singh Rajput’s death, giving a clean chit to Rhea Chakraborty. Rajput was found dead on June 14, 2020, initiating multiple probes. The closure reports in both cases have been submitted in a Mumbai court. Rhea's lawyer highlighted the hardships she faced, expressing hope that such incidents do not recur.
title: CBI closes actor Sushant Singh Rajput death case, clears Rhea
‘Hindu persecution in Bangladesh cause of concern’: RSS calls for global action

description: Jayant Patil met NCP chief Ajit Pawar for a closed-door discussion at the VSI, which was attended by Sharad Pawar. Ajit Pawar downplayed speculations about Patil quitting his party, stating that their meeting was focused on discussing the implementation of artificial intelligence in agriculture.
title: Pawar ‘peeps into’ room as Ajit, Jayant hold closed-door meeting

description: Union finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman emphasized that the Delimitation Commission will determine the criteria for delimitation, not based solely on population. She addressed concerns regarding the potential impact on southern states, criticized the DMK for distraction tactics, and clarified misconceptions around the National Education Policy.
title: Proposed panel will be final authority on delimitation: FM
Supreme Court shares video, photos of burnt cash at Justice Yashwant Varma's house

description: Uttarakhand CM Pushkar Singh Dhami outlines measures against illegal madrassas, traffic management for the Doon-Delhi expressway, and job creation to curb migration. He highlights the implementation of the Uniform Civil Code and successful hosting of the National Games as key achievements. Disaster response and Char Dham yatra planning are also detailed.
title: Will continue action against illegal madrassas, says Dhami

description: Authorities in Libreville, Gabon, detained 21 Karnataka residents holding fake business visas while trading goods. The group, comprising members of the Hakkipikki community, faces penalties but is arranging funds for their release and return to India with the support of their families and the Indian Embassy.
title: 21 Hakkipikki tribals detained in Gabon over alleged fake visa

description: A 27-year-old man from Rewa district died by suicide while live-streaming his final moments on social media, accusing his wife and mother-in-law of driving him to the act. The police have arrested the wife's mother and the wife for abetment to suicide after discovering the wife's involvement.
title: Cops to probe if wife saw man’s suicide live, but didn’t try to save

description: Satish Salian, father of Disha Salian, has petitioned the Bombay High Court for a CBI investigation into his daughter's death, citing mysterious circumstances and political involvement. He targets Shiv Sena leader Aaditya Thackeray. BJP's Narayan Rane alleges former CM Uddhav Thackeray asked him not to involve Aaditya in the case. Rane maintains Sushant Singh Rajput was murdered.
title: Disha Salian’s father moves HC for fresh probe by CBI

description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) attached 24 properties linked to accused former railway claims tribunal judge R K Mittal in a Rs 50 crore fraud case. The agency has previously acted against judges involved in bribery and fraud, highlighting the case of former Panchkula judge Sudhir Parmar and alleged liaisoning in the Chhattisgarh PDS scam.
title: ED acts against judge in Rs 50cr payout scam, seizes 24 assets

description: The ethnic conflict in Manipur has displaced thousands and disrupted children's education. Relief camps are overflowing with young minds whose dreams have been interrupted. As families struggle for survival, the future of an entire generation hangs in the balance, with urgent government intervention needed.
title: 'I had a dream': Education a casualty as camp kids stare at uncertainty

description: A Vadodara family has sought the PMO's intervention for their son's release in Qatar, where he has been held in solitary confinement since January 1 without any charges. Amit Gupta, working for an Indian multinational company, was detained after dining out, leaving his family in distress.
title: Man confined in Qatar, family seeks PM’s help
Man run over by his own car in Chhatarpur
Police assault on Army colonel in Punjab: Wife leads ex-servicemen’s protest in Patiala to demand CBI probe

description: Leaders of Kisan Mazdoor Morcha and Sanyukt Kisan Morcha (Non-Political) have opted not to file bail applications, challenging the Punjab government's commitment to detain them. Despite their arrests, leaders remain determined to continue their protest. Missing valuables and unjust treatment have added to their grievances, and farmer organizations vow to mobilize people for future demonstrations.
title: Protesting farmers dare Punjab government, refuse to seek bail

description: Hundreds of Meiteis and Kukis in Manipur, displaced by ongoing ethnic violence, appealed to a delegation of Supreme Court and High Court judges for the restoration of their homes and lands. The judges assured them of legal aid services and pledged support for their resettlement.
title: SC judges bring hope to Manipur relief camps

description: A truck loaded with liquor bottles overturned on the Purvanchal expressway near Azamgarh, revealing a smuggling operation from Rajasthan to Bihar. The crash exposed about 1,650 litres of liquor concealed under soil-filled gunny sacks. The driver fled, and police investigations continue into the broader smuggling network.
title: Truck smuggling liquor bottles to Bihar overturns on Purvanchal e-way

description: Virat Kohli reached a milestone of over 1,000 runs against Kolkata Knight Riders by scoring 59 not out, leading Royal Challengers Bengaluru to victory. Kohli's solid partnership with Phil Salt, and a strong bowling performance from RCB, enabled them to chase down the target of 175 in just 16.2 overs.
title: IPL: Kohli reaches new milestone with heroics in KKR vs RCB opener

description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) launched their IPL 2025 campaign with a seven-wicket victory against Kolkata Knight Riders (KKR) at Eden Gardens. RCB, led by Rajat Patidar, chased down 175 runs with standout performances from Phil Salt (56) and Virat Kohli (59 not out). Krunal Pandya's three-wicket haul crippled KKR, who managed 174/8 in their 20 overs.
title: Krunal Pandya's triple strike turns the tide as RCB crush KKR in IPL opener

description: Badaer Khan Suri's father who lives in India told TOI that he and his son visited Gaza only once to ask for Mapheze's hand in the marriage. Mapheze Saleh is Suri's wife, an American citizen of Palestinian descent and her father Ahmed Yousef is a former adviser to Hamas leader Ismail Haniyeh. Yousef left politics almost a decade ago.
title: We know only as much: Badar Khan Suri's sister claims family kept in the dark

description: At least three people were killed and 14 others injured in a mass shooting at Young Park in Las Cruces, New Mexico. Police are investigating the incident, with assistance from state and federal agencies, and are asking for public help to identify the suspect or suspects.
title: At least 3 killed, 14 injured in mass shooting at New Mexico park
CBI files closure report in actor Sushant Singh Rajput death case
'Want to keep granddaughter with us': Murdered Meerut man's mother
Judge 'cash at home' case: CJI orders in-house inquiry into allegations against Justice Varma

description: The arrest of Istanbul's opposition mayor Ekrem Imamoglu sparked widespread protests across Turkey. Accused of financial misconduct and links to Kurdish militants, his detention is seen as a political move against a potential challenger to President Erdogan. Thousands have taken to the streets, demanding government resignation and supporting Imamoglu, who decries his arrest as a 'coup'.
title: Turkey on boil: Why mass protests have erupted against Erdogan

description: Hardik Pandya and MS Dhoni's heartfelt hug during a training session before the IPL 2025 clash between Mumbai Indians and Chennai Super Kings at Chepauk captured the essence of camaraderie and mutual respect. Despite fierce rivalries, this moment highlighted the deep bonds formed over years, setting an emotional tone for the highly anticipated match.
title: Watch: Dhoni, Hardik's tight hugs steal the spotlight

description: Sachin Jha was compelled to close his Zerodha account due to a compliance issue when his wife joined a global investment bank. Zerodha CEO Nithin Kamath responded promptly, addressing the trust gap with an action plan, although Jha ultimately closed his account.
title: 'Close all Zerodha accounts': 'Message' that got CEO Nithin Kamath into action

description: Muskan Rastogi and Sahil Shukla, accused of murdering Muskan’s husband Saurabh Rajput, fled to Himachal Pradesh after the crime. They presented themselves as a married couple and maintained a low profile. Authorities arrested them after Muskan’s father compelled her to confess. The murder involved dismembering the body and sealing it in a cement-filled drum.
title: Dashed to the hills, kept low profile: How 'killer' Meerut wife, her lover tried to evade police

description: The Trump administration is scrutinizing federal consultancies like Booz Allen and Accenture, demanding clear reports on their government contracts and cost-cutting plans. Accenture's stock fell due to reduced US government work. The investigation aims to curb waste and spending in the $759 billion federal contract market, affecting major firms such as IBM and General Dynamics.
title: US govt sends 'warning' letter to 10 highest-paid consulting cos: Explain ...

description: Virat Kohli joined Shah Rukh Khan on stage at the IPL 2025 opening ceremony at Eden Gardens, celebrating Kohli's 18-season journey. The two stars danced together, thrilling the crowd with their camaraderie. KKR’s Rinku Singh later joined them, symbolically bridging the past, present, and future of cricket and entertainment. The evening concluded with the national anthem.
title: Watch: Virat Kohli dances with SRK in rare performance

description: A man has been booked for tricking three women into marriage by falsely claiming to be a widower and an excise department employee. He persuaded one to take a Rs 42 lakh loan. Police investigations reveal he has deceived other women previously and has a history of fraudulent marriages.
title: Lutera dulha: Man poses as 'excise officer' to dupe three women into marriage

description: Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis has stated that the losses from the Central Nagpur riot will be recovered from the rioters, including through property disposal if necessary. 92 arrests have been made, with the event possibly linked to Malegaon and international instigators, and social media users spreading hatred will face stringent action.
title: 'Will dispose properties of rioters to recover riot damages': CM Fadnavis

description: Tamil Nadu's DMK-led Joint Action Committee meeting, chaired by CM M.K. Stalin, united multiple state leaders against population-based Lok Sabha delimitation. They argue this move threatens democratic representation, particularly for southern states that have successfully implemented population control measures.
title: Amid fair delimitation push, a ‘Sword of Damocles’ warning from Kerala CM

description: The FBI has warned of a series of attacks on Tesla properties, including dealerships and charging stations, across the U.S. The attacks, involving arson and vandalism, are linked to political tensions surrounding Tesla and its CEO, Elon Musk. Authorities are investigating and prosecuting the offenders, while Tesla owners urge restraint against violence.
title: FBI issues nationwide alert over rising attacks on Tesla dealerships

description: Saurabh Rajput was brutally murdered by his wife, Muskan Rastogi, and her lover, Sahil Shukla, dismembering his body and sealing it in a cement drum. They manipulated family and friends, even taking a vacation post-murder. Muskan's parents called for capital punishment, and both culprits were arrested and charged with murder and destruction of evidence.
title: Head severed, legs bent back: Autopsy reveals savagery of Meerut killing

description: Ramesh Shanmugam, a para-athlete from Tamil Nadu, has excelled in wheelchair racing despite losing his legs in a childhood accident. Inspired by MS Dhoni, Shanmugam secured multiple medals at the World Para Athletics Grand Prix and Khelo India Para Games. With support from authorities, he aims to represent India in the Paralympics.
title: 'Once MS Dhoni retires, I will stop watching cricket'

description: George Foreman's journey from a heavyweight champion to a preacher and back to the boxing ring is highlighted. His determination to regain his title after a long hiatus and the challenges faced along the way are detailed, culminating in his eventual victory at 42 years old.
title: Big George and the legacy of big black men

description: Heathrow Airport resumes full operations following a severe power outage caused by a fire at a nearby electrical substation, which led to the cancellation and diversion of 1,350 flights affecting around 200,000 passengers. The economic impact includes an estimated loss of £4.8 million per day in tourism revenue.
title: Heathrow Airport 'open and fully operational' a day after fire shutdown

description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un affirmed his support for Russia's war in Ukraine during a meeting with Russian official Sergei Shoigu. Kim pledged unwavering support for Russia's sovereignty and security, while Shoigu conveyed Russian President Vladimir Putin's greetings and commitment to their mutual defence treaty.
title: 'Invariable support': North Korea's Kim Jong Un backs Russia in Ukraine war

description: Following an assassination attempt on Donald Trump, Russian President Vladimir Putin visited his church to pray for Trump and demonstrated goodwill through personal gestures. Steve Witkoff highlighted Trump's approach to diplomatic engagement with Russia and Putin’s positive response to negotiating the end of the Ukraine conflict, emphasizing Trump's leadership.
title: ‘Met his priest’: Putin 'prayed' for Trump after shooting, top US envoy reveals

description: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella showed interest in the new hybrid sport 'Crennis' after a playful video featuring Bill Gates and Sachin Tendulkar playing the game was shared. Combining cricket and tennis, the video highlighted their fun interaction and ended with them enjoying vada pav. The collaboration hints at future projects between the Sachin Tendulkar Foundation & Gates Foundation.
title: Microsoft CEO on Sachin and Bill Gates video: Looks like I found ...

description: A PAC funded by Elon Musk is offering Wisconsin voters financial incentives to sign a petition opposing activist judges ahead of a key state Supreme Court election. The move aims to support the Republican-favored candidate, Brad Schimel, potentially impacting the judiciary's balance of power.
title: Musk-backed PAC offers voters $100 to sign petition against 'activist judges'
'No delimitation till 2050': Stalin-led JAC to sumbit letter to PM Modi
'Publicity rather than delivery': Kharge attacks Centre over 'Make in India'

description: Congress MP Jairam Ramesh criticised Prime Minister Narendra Modi for not visiting Manipur since violence erupted nearly two years ago, highlighting the need for a healing touch. He also questioned the delay in imposing President's rule despite constitutional collapse and criticised Home Minister Amit Shah's lack of response on the situation in Manipur.
title: Supreme Court judges visit Manipur, Jairam Ramesh asks 'when will PM Modi go?'
The Trump Organisation enters real estate in India with Rs 2,500-cr Pune project

description: Denmark's travel advisory page says transgender Danes should first consult the US embassy before traveling to the US. Finland issued a similar warning for its citizens last week in light of President Trump's policies.
title: Transgender Danes told to consult US embassy before travel

description: Maharashtra CM Fadnavis reviewed the communal violence in Nagpur due to the Aurangzeb tomb row. He emphasized that rioters would bear the costs of damages, with assets sold if necessary. The unrest included stone-pelting after rumors of a Quran verse burning. Over 100 arrests have been made, and social media posts inciting violence have been deleted.
title: 'Will use bulldozers if ...': CM Fadnavis' warning to Nagpur rioters

description: Neo-Nazis march in Budapest with impunity, while Hungary's government cracks down on LGBTQ+ representation, banning Pride parades and fining a bookstore for displaying LGBTQ+ content. Prime Minister Orban faces growing criticism for corruption, nepotism, and repression, with opposition leader Peter Magyar gaining popularity.
title: As Hungary bans pride events, critics fear Russian influence

description: The 18th edition of the IPL kicks off with significant changes, including seven new captains, updated rules like the return of saliva to shine the ball, and new coaching appointments. Notable captains include Rajat Patidar for RCB and Axar Patel for Delhi Capitals. There's heightened anticipation surrounding big-money signing Rishabh Pant at Lucknow Super Giants.
title: IPL 2025: Talking points and everything you need to know

description: Israel's High Court of Justice has temporarily blocked the removal of Ronen Bar, head of Israel's internal security agency Shin Bet, pending an appeal hearing. Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's move to sack Bar has sparked widespread protests in Israel.
title: Israel's top court blocks dismissal of Shin Bet chief after removal by cabinet

description: Chief ministers from various states gathered in Chennai to oppose the Centre's proposed delimitation of parliamentary seats. Tamil Nadu CM MK Stalin emphasized the potential legal battle, while Kerala CM Pinarayi Vijayan criticized the move as politically motivated. An expert panel for fair delimitation was proposed.
title: 'North will make us secondary citizens': Telangana CM Revanth Reddy

description: A Supreme Court delegation, led by Justice BR Gavai, has reached Manipur's Imphal to inspect relief camps amid ongoing ethnic violence. Their visit aims to assess and boost legal and humanitarian aid. Authorities are addressing a recent tragic incident involving the suspected rape and murder of a nine-year-old girl in a Churachandpur relief camp.
title: Supreme Court judges reach Manipur to assess relief efforts

description: The United States Department of Homeland Security has revoked legal safeguards for over 530,000 immigrants from these four countries who have been in the US since October 2022. The directive impacts those under the humanitarian parole program.
title: US ends legal status for 532,000 immigrants

description: A viral video shows vendors repackaging rotten strawberries as fresh, posing serious health risks. Consuming these can lead to food poisoning, liver damage, respiratory issues, and fungal infections. These practices highlight a lack of oversight by food safety authorities. People are advised to avoid moldy strawberries and ensure they're consuming fresh produce to avoid health complications.
title: Viral: Rotten, fungus-grown strawberries cleaned and repackaged- Watch video

description: Boxing legend George Foreman has died at 76. Remembered for his epic bouts with Muhammad Ali and his later business success with the George Foreman Grill, Foreman also made a remarkable comeback to regain the heavyweight title at age 45, securing his place in boxing history.
title: Watch: George Foreman vs Muhammad Ali in epic ‘Rumble in the Jungle’ fight

description: NCP MP Supriya Sule criticises Air India's flight delays, urging the Civil Aviation Minister to act. Sule shared her own experience of a delayed flight, highlighting the impact on passengers. Separately, a Mohali consumer court fined Air India Rs 60,500 for delaying a refund and ordered compensation for a passenger.
title: 'We pay premium fares, unacceptable': Supriya Sule slams Air India

description: Maharashtra deputy chief minister Ajit Pawar has warned against attempts to intimidate the Muslim community or create communal discord, asserting they will face serious consequences. Speaking at an iftar party in Mumbai, Pawar emphasized unity and assured his support for the community, referencing the recent Nagpur violence amid protests against Mughal emperor Aurangzeb's tomb.
title: 'Will not be spared': Ajit Pawar threatens those intimidating Muslims

description: Muskaan Rastogi and Sahil Shukla, after murdering Muskaan's husband Saurabh, were seen celebrating Holi and Muskaan's birthday. The case, involving Saurabh's disappearance and subsequent discovery of his decomposed body, unfolded that Muskaan had manipulated Sahil. Both have been charged with murder. Muskaan's parents demand strict punishment, citing her as a danger to society.
title: Muskaan Rastogi celebrated birthday, Holi with lover days after husband's murder

description: Former heavyweight boxing champion George Foreman passed away at age 76. Known for his 1968 Olympic gold and world titles in 1973 and 1994, Foreman was famous for his bouts with Joe Frazier and Muhammad Ali. Beyond boxing, he gained fame for his grilling machine. He left behind a legacy in sports and business.
title: Boxing legend George Foreman dies at 76

description: Andrew and Tristan Tate have returned to Romania to face charges of human trafficking and forming a criminal gang, asserting their innocence. The investigation is ongoing with additional charges including human trafficking and money laundering, although the brothers deny all allegations.
title: 'Innocent men don’t run from anything': Tates return to Romania

description: Police in Nagpur have arrested 105 individuals, including 10 minors, after violence erupted due to rumors about the burning of a sacred 'chadar'. Special teams have been formed to identify more suspects, and primary instigator Fahim Khan has been charged with sedition and other offenses.
title: Nagpur violence: MDP president among fresh arrests by police; 10 minors held

description: Dilip Ghosh threatened a woman protester who questioned his involvement in construction of a road in Kharagpur, even as the ex-BJP MP claimed he provided the funds for the road during his tenure as an MP. Local councillor Pradip Sarkar condemned Ghosh's behaviour, criticizing his aggressive and disrespectful remarks towards the women.
title: Watch: Dilip Ghosh threatens to 'choke' woman who confronted him

description: A 21-year-old woman from Juhapura has filed a complaint against her husband and in-laws for harassment, compelled clothing choices, and verbal abuse post-marriage. Her husband's alcohol habit and resulting abuse were supported by his parents, leading her to seek police intervention.
title: Forced to wear nightgown all day, woman files complaint in Ahmedabad

description: Amazon has begun charging a non-refundable Rs 49 processing fee for Instant Bank Discounts of Rs 500 or more, affecting all customers including Prime members. This fee is intended to cover the costs of handling bank discount offers and will impact overall savings for purchases.
title: Amazon is now charging processing fee on discount offers, here's how much is it

description: RJD workers have placed a poster outside former CM Rabri Devi's residence, portraying current Bihar CM Nitish Kumar as a villain for allegedly disrespecting women, Mahatma Gandhi, and the national anthem. The controversy follows an incident where Kumar was seen talking during the national anthem. Tejashwi Yadav criticized Kumar via social media as Bihar prepares for assembly elections.
title: Another RJD poster targets Nitish Kumar as ‘khalnayak’ outside Lalu's residence

description: A woman in Greater Noida died from rabies after drinking unboiled milk from an infected cow. The cow had rabies from a stray dog bite. The woman experienced symptoms days after consuming the milk and was turned away by several hospitals. Immediate vaccination after any potential exposure to rabies is crucial as the infection is fatal once symptoms appear.
title: Woman dies of rabies days after drinking milk from infected cow: Report
After metal fence, ASI installs barbed wire at Aurangzeb’s tomb

description: Chandrayaan-3's Chandra's Surface Thermophysical Experiment (ChaSTE) achieved unprecedented in-situ temperature measurements at the Moon's south pole, revealing higher than expected surface temperatures. These findings are crucial for understanding lunar thermophysics and potential water-ice deposits, which are essential for human habitat and exploration. The research, bridging critical knowledge gaps, was published in Nature Communications Earth & Environment.
title: Finding water-ice on Moon: Chandrayaan-3 unlocks some 'hot' secrets

description: A 78-year-old woman, Rajbala Devi, died in Achharonda village after accidentally consuming acid, mistaking it for water. She had been suffering from depression following her husband's death. The incident occurred on Thursday, and while no FIR has been filed, the police are investigating the presence of the acid bottle in her home.
title: Mistaking acid for water, woman dies in Meerut following husband's death

description: Television stars Aly Goni and Jasmin Bhasin are excited about their decision to move in together after five years. They shared their joyful anticipation and the challenges they faced in finding and setting up a new home, marking a significant milestone in their relationship.
title: Aly Goni and Jasmin Bhasin announce moving in together after 5yrs of dating

description: Elon Musk discussed his use of ketamine for depression, highlighting its necessity for managing his mental health while maintaining his work ethic. He defended his late-night social media activity, asserted improvements in X's advertising revenue, and addressed content moderation policies. Musk's interview with Don Lemon led to the termination of Lemon's deal with X, reflecting tensions with traditional media.
title: Elon Musk defends Ketamine use: It helps me, and that helps Tesla
India hits out at Pakistan for hosting Zakir Naik

description: RJD workers have placed a poster outside former CM Rabri Devi's residence, portraying current Bihar CM Nitish Kumar as a villain for allegedly disrespecting women, Mahatma Gandhi, and the national anthem. The controversy follows an incident where Kumar was seen talking during the national anthem. Tejashwi Yadav criticized Kumar via social media as Bihar prepares for assembly elections.
title: 'Nayak nahi khalnayak hu main': RJD targets Nitish with another poster

description: Voice of America has filed a lawsuit alleging that the Trump administration unlawfully shut down the news organisation. The lawsuit claims that this action deprived many regions of an important source of objective news, with the closure attributed to political bias allegations.
title: 'Objective news gone from world': Voice of America says 'unlawfully shut down'

description: Tamil Nadu chief minister MK Stalin initiated the first meeting of the Joint Action Committee to oppose the Centre’s proposed delimitation exercise. Stalin emphasized the importance of this event for safeguarding India's federal structure and warned about potential adverse effects on states' rights and parliamentary representation.
title: 'Today will be etched in history': Stalin kicks off JAC meeting on delimitation

description: A Norwegian man, Arve Hjalmar Holmen, lodged a complaint after ChatGPT falsely claimed he murdered two of his children. Digital rights group Noyb alleges this breaches GDPR regulations. OpenAI acknowledged the issue, noting improvements in newer ChatGPT versions to enhance data accuracy.
title: ChatGPT tells a father he murdered his own children

description: Amid all the talk of team dynamics, the T20 league’s 18th season will also be about individual skills, match-ups, split-second decisions and unique subplots.
title: IPL 2025’s star attraction: The battles within battles

description: Shah Rukh Khan electrified fans as he arrived in Kolkata for the IPL's opening match. Amidst the ecstatic greeting at Eden Gardens, SRK showcased his belief that he's his team's lucky charm. He is currently working on his action-packed film 'King' with daughter Suhana Khan.
title: SRK sparks frenzy at Kolkata airport; blows kisses to fans- Watch

description: The John Abraham starrer The Diplomat opened with promise but saw its earnings decline, amassing Rs 20.40 crore in its second week. Despite initial setbacks, including rejections from OTT platforms, the film remained profitable due to its Rs 20 crore budget. It outperformed the Hollywood release Snow White, generating significant interest among fans.
title: The Diplomat: John Abraham starrer opens week 2 with low Rs 1.25 crore

description: Vicky Kaushal's Chhaava enters its fifth week with a stellar box office collection of Rs 575 crore, despite competition from new releases and controversies. The film, based on Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj's life, has faced piracy issues, with legal action being taken against those responsible.
title: Vicky Kaushal's Chhaava emerges highest-earning with Rs 2.10 cr
With Bihar polls coming, BJP wary of Nitish's 'erratic behaviour'
Woman who accused minister Jaykumar Gore of harassment held for extortion
Minister says Allahabad HC ruling on child assault 'has no place in civilised society'

description: A two-and-a-half-year-old girl was raped by a neighbor in Satna town on Thursday. The accused lured the toddler, and after being sexually assaulted, she informed her mother. The family reported the incident, leading to the perpetrator's arrest under the Pocso Act. State Congress president Jitu Patwari criticized the government's response to crimes against women.
title: 'Came out weeping': Two-and-a half year old girl raped in Madhya Pradesh

description: Columbia University agreed to policy changes after the Trump administration froze $400 million in federal funding over antisemitism concerns. Measures include a mask ban, new disciplinary protocols, and campus police authority to make arrests. The university will also appoint new leadership and develop a K-12 curriculum on antisemitism to address the situation.
title: Columbia University agrees to policy changes amid 'anti-semitism' row

description: Stephen A. Smith, previously critical of Bronny James, has changed his stance after Bronny's impressive performance against the Milwaukee Bucks. Smith acknowledged Bronny's elevated confidence and poise, crediting the Lakers' coaching staff for his development, while reiterating his unchanged views on LeBron's influence.
title: 'He looked like somebody that belonged': Stephen A. Smith'S u-turn on Bronny James

description: Rajat Patidar returns to Eden Gardens, where his career soared in 2022. Now captaining for the first time in IPL, Patidar faces pressure to lead RCB to their first trophy. KKR, under new skipper Ajinkya Rahane, who boasts an impressive international leadership record but mixed IPL captaincy results, aims to defend their title amid significant team changes.
title: IPL 2025, KKR vs RCB: New leaders, fresh start

description: Prominent Baloch activist Mahrang Baloch has condemned Pakistani security forces for opening fire on peaceful protesters in Quetta, causing injuries and one death. At the UNHRC session in Geneva, the repression in Balochistan was highlighted, including enforced disappearances, targeted killings, and intimidation tactics against political activists and human rights defenders.
title: 'Pakistani security forces fired on protesters in Quetta, one dead'

description: Passengers at London’s Heathrow Airport faced major disruption as fires broke out at the electrical substation, causing flights to be diverted midair. This led to significant delays, including for comedian Adam Conover. British Airways passengers at JFK in New York also experienced long queues and confusion while trying to rebook flights. Heathrow's CEO assured operations would resume by Saturday.
title: 'We don’t want to be here anymore': Passengers left annoyed at Heathrow Airport

description: Indian nationals abroad are expected to comply with local laws and regulations, says the Indian government as authorities detain Badar Khan Suri and Ranjini Srinivasan faces visa cancellation. MEA spokesperson Randhir Jaiswal emphasizes that neither approached Indian authorities for assistance. Suri was detained for allegedly spreading 'Hamas propaganda'. The government underscores respect for sovereign immigration policies.
title: MEA advise to Indians abroad: Comply with local laws and regulations

description: JJP leader Ravinder Minna was shot dead in Panipat on Friday, with his cousin and another person also injured in the attack. Five police teams have been formed to apprehend the accused. This incident follows the killing of BJP leader Surendra Jawahra in Sonipat over a land dispute.
title: Haryana: JJP leader Ravinder Minna shot dead in Panipat

description: British Airways resumed operations at Heathrow Airport after an 18-hour disruption caused by a severe electrical substation fire. The incident led to mass flight cancellations, affecting around 200,000 passengers and highlighting concerns about the resilience of Britain's infrastructure.
title: Heathrow Airport back to life: First flight touches down after 18-hour shutdown

description: Persistent drizzle interrupted practice sessions of KKR and RCB at Eden Gardens, ahead of their IPL 2025 opener. The Indian Meteorological Department has warned of severe weather including thundersqualls and moderate rainfall, potentially disrupting the planned opening ceremony and match schedules.
title: IPL 2025: Will KKR vs RCB be spoiled by rain in Kolkata?

description: Israel's military has eliminated Osama Tabash, the head of Hamas's military intelligence in southern Gaza, in an airstrike. Tabash, a veteran member of Hamas, was responsible for significant intelligence and strategic operations in the region. His death is considered a major blow to Hamas's intelligence and operational capabilities in the ongoing conflict.
title: Israel kills Hamas military intelligence chief Osama Tabash in Gaza

description: Taylor Swift has been inadvertently drawn into a legal dispute between Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni over the film It Ends With Us. Though not involved with the movie's production, her connection to Lively has made her a topic in the controversy, much to her displeasure.
title: Taylor Swift frustrated over involvement in 'It ends with us' legal dispute

description: The UK government considers reducing or eliminating its Digital Services Tax by April to avoid potential US tariffs. Prime Minister Keir Starmer's administration faces a tough decision balancing revenue gains against risks of trade penalties while addressing criticism from Labour MPs.
title: UK plans to end the tax Google, Apple, and Microsoft 'hate', and reason is

description: Nadir Shah, a gangster-turned-businessman, was murdered in front of a gym in GK-I, with several Special Cell officers nearby. The Greater Kailash police were kept from investigating, raising suspicions and questions about the involvement or oversight of the special cell.
title: Was special cell stalking gangster Nadir Shah before and during his murder in Greater Kailash-1 last Sept?

description: Elon Musk's visit to the Pentagon sparked controversy after false reports claimed he would discuss US strategies for a potential conflict with China. President Trump and Defense Secretary Hegseth clarified the meeting was about innovation and efficiencies, with no discussion on China.
title: Donald Trump on Elon Musk's Pentagon visit: He will leave the room if...

description: A 38-year-old software engineer from Chandannagar, Pune, was arrested for killing his young son due to frequent disputes with his wife. Madhava Sadhurao Tiketi, a former techie from IIT Bengaluru, admitted to committing the murder as police discovered the boy’s body and the murder weapon. Tiketi had been heavily inebriated when captured.
title: 'In single swipe': Techie slits throat of 3-yr-old son over disputes with wife

description: A passenger's row of seats on an IndiGo flight from Delhi to Lucknow became loose mid-flight, causing a terrifying experience. The airline has apologized and announced an investigation into this rare maintenance issue to prevent any future occurrences.
title: 'Mini heart attack': IndiGo flyer stunned as seat becomes loose mid-air

description: Chief Justice of India Sanjiv Khanna sought a report from Delhi High Court Chief Justice D K Upadhyay regarding the recovery of cash from Justice Yashwant Varma's residence. The CJI will consider setting up an inquiry panel based on the findings. Justice Varma was recently transferred back to Allahabad HC.
title: Cash recovery at judge Yashwant Varma’s home: CJI may decide on inquiry today

description: The lion population in Gujarat is expected to reach between 900 and 1,500 in the 2025 census due to conservation efforts. The 2020 census recorded 674 lions, but informal estimates suggest much higher numbers. The lion territory has expanded by 36% in five years. Officials choose conservative reporting to account for factors like high cub mortality.
title: Official lion count in Gujarat likely to hit 900 mark in 2025 census
